# TypeScript: Avoid Namespaces

1. Do not use `namespace` or `module` for code organization; prefer ES modules.
2. Namespaces are legacy and unnecessary with modern module systems.

```typescript
// Good
// Use ES module imports/exports
export function foo() {}

// Bad
namespace MyNamespace {
  export function foo() {}
}
```
